sentences: Olalekan Babalola (born c. 1960) is a Nigerian jazz percussionist and musician.
In 1980, he left Nigeria for the United Kingdom to study automobile engineering at the Chelsea College of Aeronautical and Automobile Engineering after he won a Lagos State Scholarship.
In 2006, he became Nigeria's first Grammy Award winner for his work on Ali Farka Touré's In the Heart of the Moon which he was credited in three tracks.
He also won a second Grammy in 2009 for his work on Cassandra Wilson's 2008 album titled Loverly.
